description:
Roles & Responsibilities
Job Duties:
The activities required to be performed shall include the following:
Requirements gathering and writing of specifications;
Administration of SP’s websites, web portals and other systems;
Maintenance support of existing and new websites, web portals and other systems, including the resolution of day-to-day issues;
Project and vendor management and quality assurance of deliverables;

Job Requirements:

The qualification and work experience required are as follows:
Minimum 1 years of hands-on experience using CMS like WordPress, Sitefinity, etc.;
Minimum 3 years in developing websites using HTML, JavaScript and CSS
Knowledge of .NET Core or ASP.Net development will be a bonus.
Administration experience with SharePoint will be a bonus;
Experience in Agile Development and Project Management is preferred.

Interested applicants may apply with detailed CV and send to patrina@eps.com.sg stating your expected salary and availability.

Roles & Responsibilities
Accedo develops applications and solutions for the Television, Broadcast and Streaming industry, providing a range of engineering challenges for our Development Teams. We offer a portfolio of experience-centric video solutions that enable our customers to monetise video and transform video services to meet rapidly changing consumer expectations and compete better. Accedo customers include over 350 of the world's leading video service providers, such as SBS On Demand, ABC iView, 7Plus, Foxtel, Telstra, HBO, NBC Universal, StarHub, among many others.

What we are looking for

Accedo is looking for a talented Senior Software Engineer (Web) to join its growing Professional Services team in Singapore . At Accedo, you will be part of a diverse and multi-disciplined team, gaining exposure to cutting edge technologies and can work with some of the largest global media brands in the industry. Working in a highly collaborative environment, you will help transform requirements and designs into high performing and feature-rich applications on a wide variety of web-based platforms and devices.
You will play a key role in designing, building and maintaining large-scale, high availability Smart TV, Console and Web applications for various platforms.
Ensure development best practices are followed (Clean Code, Clean Architecture, code reviews, improve CI/CD).
A pivotal role in communicating and coordinating with project managers, team members, and clients.
Responsibilities
Strong Web development experience, with a demonstrable track record of Web project delivery;
Good understanding of development methodologies, testing practices, and tools and knowing when to apply each method to achieve the desired outcomes;
Strong experience and knowledge of Design and Architectural patterns and knows when to apply them;
A strong understanding of modern Javascript frameworks and development;
Strong communication skills and knows when to ask for help and bounce ideas and solutions off peers;
Experience providing technical leadership and mentorship to fellow developers;
Communication and engagement with clients on an operational to tactical level.
Requirements
Degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, IT or related discipline, or comparable experience;
3-10 years' work experience in a similar capacity;
Expert at deploying modern web technologies like React, TypeScript or JavaScript, HTML5, CSS etc.;
Great communications skills in English;
Proficient with source code management (Git/Bitbucket/GitHub);
Experience with Agile development methodologies, e.g. Scrum, TDD;
Proficiency in CI/CD concepts like Build Automation, Automated Quality Gates and Automated Deployments;
Good knowledge of performance and memory optimisations, proficient usage of the tools available in SDK's and excellent debugging skills for web platforms in question;
Experience with cloud platforms like AWS is beneficial;
Interest in learning new platforms and new technologies is a big plus.
Understanding of VOD, live streaming, and DRM, as well as experience in the TV industry (IPTV, Connected TV), is a plus.
